.TH VOIX 1 "December 2025" "1.0.0" "Voix User Manual"
.SH NAME
voix \- simple privilege escalation tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B voix
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs...\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Voix
is a lightweight, secure replacement for \fBsudo\fR and \fBdoas\fR designed for modern Linux systems.
It provides privilege escalation with comprehensive security checks and configurable user permissions.
.PP
Voix executes commands with elevated privileges while maintaining strict security validation
and audit logging. It supports user-specific command permissions and multiple target users.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.BI \-u " user" ", " \-\-user " user"
Execute command as specified user (default: root).
.TP
.BI \-c " config" ", " \-\-config " config"
Use specified configuration file instead of default.
.SH COMMANDS
Execute any command with elevated privileges as configured.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List root directory:
.B voix ls /root
.TP
Restart service as admin user:
.B voix \-u admin systemctl restart nginx
.TP
Update system packages:
.B voix apt update
.TP
Execute with custom config:
.B voix \-c /etc/voix\-custom.conf systemctl status
.SH CONFIGURATION
Voix reads configuration from \fI/etc/voix.conf\fR by default.
.PP
Configuration format:
.PP
.nf
.RS
# Global settings
key = value

# User permissions
username:command1,command2,command3

# Allowed users
allowed_users = user1,user2,user3
.RE
.fi
.PP
Example configuration:
.PP
.nf
.RS
# Allow root all commands
root:*

# Allow admin system commands
admin:systemctl,apt,yum,dnf,ls,cat,grep

# Specify allowed users
allowed_users = root,admin,deploy
.RE
.fi
.SH SECURITY
Voix implements comprehensive security measures:
.IP \(bu 2
Blocks dangerous commands (su, sudo, bash, etc.)
.IP \(bu 2
Validates path safety (prevents traversal attacks)
.IP \(bu 2
Filters shell metacharacters (prevents injection)
.IP \(bu 2
Validates user permissions
.IP \(bu 2
Provides audit logging
.SH FILES
.I /etc/voix.conf
.RS
Default configuration file.
.RE
.PP
.I /var/log/voix.log
.RS
Audit log file.
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Command executed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
General error (permission denied, invalid command, etc.).
.TP
.B \-1
System error (fork failed, etc.).
